44#define bioslog(lvl, fmt, args...) do { \
45 nvkm_printk(init->subdev, lvl, info, "0x%04x[%c]: "fmt, \
46 init->offset, init_exec(init) ? \
47 '0' + (init->nested - 1) : ' ', ##args); \
48} while(0)
49#define cont(fmt, args...) do { \
50 if (init->subdev->debug >= NV_DBG_TRACE) \
51 printk(fmt, ##args); \
52} while(0)
53#define trace(fmt, args...) bioslog(TRACE, fmt, ##args)
54#define warn(fmt, args...) bioslog(WARN, fmt, ##args)
55#define error(fmt, args...) bioslog(ERROR, fmt, ##args)

61static inline bool
62init_exec(struct nvbios_init *init)
63{
64 return (init->execute == 1) || ((init->execute & 5) == 5);
65}
66
67static inline void
68init_exec_set(struct nvbios_init *init, bool exec)
69{
70 if (exec) init->execute &= 0xfd;
71 else init->execute |= 0x02;
72}
73
74static inline void
75init_exec_inv(struct nvbios_init *init)
76{
77 init->execute ^= 0x02;
78}
79
80static inline void
81init_exec_force(struct nvbios_init *init, bool exec)
82{
83 if (exec) init->execute |= 0x04;
84 else init->execute &= 0xfb;
85}

88 * init parser wrappers for normal register/i2c/whatever accessors

91static inline int
92init_or(struct nvbios_init *init)
93{
94 if (init_exec(init)) {
95 if (init->outp)
96 return ffs(init->outp->or) - 1;
97 error("script needs OR!!\n");
98 }
99 return 0;
100}
101
102static inline int
103init_link(struct nvbios_init *init)
104{
105 if (init_exec(init)) {
106 if (init->outp)
107 return !(init->outp->sorconf.link & 1);
108 error("script needs OR link\n");
109 }
110 return 0;
111}

113static inline int
114init_crtc(struct nvbios_init *init)
115{
116 if (init_exec(init)) {
117 if (init->crtc >= 0)
118 return init->crtc;
119 error("script needs crtc\n");
120 }
121 return 0;
122}

124static u8
125init_conn(struct nvbios_init *init)
126{
127 struct nvkm_bios *bios = init->bios;
128 struct nvbios_connE connE;
129 u8 ver, hdr;
130 u32 conn;
131
132 if (init_exec(init)) {
133 if (init->outp) {
134 conn = init->outp->connector;
135 conn = nvbios_connEp(bios, conn, &ver, &hdr, &connE);
136 if (conn)
137 return connE.type;
138 }
139
140 error("script needs connector type\n");
141 }
142
143 return 0xff;
144}

146static inline u32
147init_nvreg(struct nvbios_init *init, u32 reg)
148{
149 struct nvkm_devinit *devinit = init->bios->subdev.device->devinit;
150
151 /* C51 (at least) sometimes has the lower bits set which the VBIOS
152 * interprets to mean that access needs to go through certain IO
153 * ports instead. The NVIDIA binary driver has been seen to access
154 * these through the NV register address, so lets assume we can
155 * do the same
156 */
157 reg &= ~0x00000003;
158
159 /* GF8+ display scripts need register addresses mangled a bit to
160 * select a specific CRTC/OR
161 */
162 if (init->bios->subdev.device->card_type >= NV_50) {
163 if (reg & 0x80000000) {
164 reg += init_crtc(init) * 0x800;
165 reg &= ~0x80000000;
166 }
167
168 if (reg & 0x40000000) {
169 reg += init_or(init) * 0x800;
170 reg &= ~0x40000000;
171 if (reg & 0x20000000) {
172 reg += init_link(init) * 0x80;
173 reg &= ~0x20000000;
174 }
175 }
176 }
177
178 if (reg & ~0x00fffffc)
179 warn("unknown bits in register 0x%08x\n", reg);
180
181 return nvkm_devinit_mmio(devinit, reg);
182}
183
184static u32
185init_rd32(struct nvbios_init *init, u32 reg)
186{
187 struct nvkm_device *device = init->bios->subdev.device;
188 reg = init_nvreg(init, reg);
189 if (reg != ~0 && init_exec(init))
190 return nvkm_rd32(device, reg);
191 return 0x00000000;
192}
193
194static void
195init_wr32(struct nvbios_init *init, u32 reg, u32 val)
196{
197 struct nvkm_device *device = init->bios->subdev.device;
198 reg = init_nvreg(init, reg);
199 if (reg != ~0 && init_exec(init))
200 nvkm_wr32(device, reg, val);
201}
202
203static u32
204init_mask(struct nvbios_init *init, u32 reg, u32 mask, u32 val)
205{
206 struct nvkm_device *device = init->bios->subdev.device;
207 reg = init_nvreg(init, reg);
208 if (reg != ~0 && init_exec(init)) {
209 u32 tmp = nvkm_rd32(device, reg);
210 nvkm_wr32(device, reg, (tmp & ~mask) | val);
211 return tmp;
212 }
213 return 0x00000000;
214}

231static u8
232init_rdvgai(struct nvbios_init *init, u16 port, u8 index)
233{
234 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = init->subdev;
235 if (init_exec(init)) {
236 int head = init->crtc < 0 ? 0 : init->crtc;
237 return nvkm_rdvgai(subdev->device, head, port, index);
238 }
239 return 0x00;
240}
241
242static void
243init_wrvgai(struct nvbios_init *init, u16 port, u8 index, u8 value)
244{
245 struct nvkm_device *device = init->subdev->device;
246
247 /* force head 0 for updates to cr44, it only exists on first head */
248 if (device->card_type < NV_50) {
249 if (port == 0x03d4 && index == 0x44)
250 init->crtc = 0;
251 }
252
253 if (init_exec(init)) {
254 int head = init->crtc < 0 ? 0 : init->crtc;
255 nvkm_wrvgai(device, head, port, index, value);
256 }
257
258 /* select head 1 if cr44 write selected it */
259 if (device->card_type < NV_50) {
260 if (port == 0x03d4 && index == 0x44 && value == 3)
261 init->crtc = 1;
262 }
263}

265static struct i2c_adapter *
266init_i2c(struct nvbios_init *init, int index)
267{
268 struct nvkm_i2c *i2c = init->bios->subdev.device->i2c;
269 struct nvkm_i2c_bus *bus;
270
271 if (index == 0xff) {
272 index = NVKM_I2C_BUS_PRI;
273 if (init->outp && init->outp->i2c_upper_default)
274 index = NVKM_I2C_BUS_SEC;
275 } else
276 if (index == 0x80) {
277 index = NVKM_I2C_BUS_PRI;
278 } else
279 if (index == 0x81) {
280 index = NVKM_I2C_BUS_SEC;
281 }
282
283 bus = nvkm_i2c_bus_find(i2c, index);
284 return bus ? &bus->i2c : NULL;
285}

306init_aux(struct nvbios_init *init)

317static u8
318init_rdauxr(struct nvbios_init *init, u32 addr)
319{
320 struct nvkm_i2c_aux *aux = init_aux(init);
321 u8 data;
322
323 if (aux && init_exec(init)) {
324 int ret = nvkm_rdaux(aux, addr, &data, 1);
325 if (ret == 0)
326 return data;
327 trace("auxch read failed with %d\n", ret);
328 }
329
330 return 0x00;
331}

334init_wrauxr(struct nvbios_init *init, u32 addr, u8 data)

336 struct nvkm_i2c_aux *aux = init_aux(init);
337 if (aux && init_exec(init)) {
338 int ret = nvkm_wraux(aux, addr, &data, 1);
339 if (ret)
340 trace("auxch write failed with %d\n", ret);
341 return ret;
342 }
343 return -ENODEV;

357/******************************************************************************
358 * parsing of bios structures that are required to execute init tables
359 *****************************************************************************/
360
361static u16
362init_table(struct nvkm_bios *bios, u16 *len)
363{
364 struct bit_entry bit_I;
365
366 if (!bit_entry(bios, 'I', &bit_I)) {
367 *len = bit_I.length;
368 return bit_I.offset;
369 }
370
371 if (bmp_version(bios) >= 0x0510) {
372 *len = 14;
373 return bios->bmp_offset + 75;
374 }
375
376 return 0x0000;
377}
378
379static u16
380init_table_(struct nvbios_init *init, u16 offset, const char *name)
381{
382 struct nvkm_bios *bios = init->bios;
383 u16 len, data = init_table(bios, &len);
384 if (data) {
385 if (len >= offset + 2) {
386 data = nvbios_rd16(bios, data + offset);
387 if (data)
388 return data;
389
390 warn("%s pointer invalid\n", name);
391 return 0x0000;
392 }
393
394 warn("init data too short for %s pointer", name);
395 return 0x0000;
396 }
397
398 warn("init data not found\n");
399 return 0x0000;
400}
401
402#define init_script_table(b) init_table_((b), 0x00, "script table")
403#define init_macro_index_table(b) init_table_((b), 0x02, "macro index table")
404#define init_macro_table(b) init_table_((b), 0x04, "macro table")
405#define init_condition_table(b) init_table_((b), 0x06, "condition table")
406#define init_io_condition_table(b) init_table_((b), 0x08, "io condition table")
407#define init_io_flag_condition_table(b) init_table_((b), 0x0a, "io flag conditon table")
408#define init_function_table(b) init_table_((b), 0x0c, "function table")
409#define init_xlat_table(b) init_table_((b), 0x10, "xlat table");
410
411static u16
412init_script(struct nvkm_bios *bios, int index)
413{
414 struct nvbios_init init = { .bios = bios };
415 u16 bmp_ver = bmp_version(bios), data;
416
417 if (bmp_ver && bmp_ver < 0x0510) {
418 if (index > 1 || bmp_ver < 0x0100)
419 return 0x0000;
420
421 data = bios->bmp_offset + (bmp_ver < 0x0200 ? 14 : 18);
422 return nvbios_rd16(bios, data + (index * 2));
423 }
424
425 data = init_script_table(&init);
426 if (data)
427 return nvbios_rd16(bios, data + (index * 2));
428
429 return 0x0000;
430}
431
432static u16
433init_unknown_script(struct nvkm_bios *bios)
434{
435 u16 len, data = init_table(bios, &len);
436 if (data && len >= 16)
437 return nvbios_rd16(bios, data + 14);
438 return 0x0000;
439}

441static u8
442init_ram_restrict_group_count(struct nvbios_init *init)
443{
444 return nvbios_ramcfg_count(init->bios);
445}

447static u8
448init_ram_restrict(struct nvbios_init *init)
449{
450 /* This appears to be the behaviour of the VBIOS parser, and *is*
451 * important to cache the NV_PEXTDEV_BOOT0 on later chipsets to
452 * avoid fucking up the memory controller (somehow) by reading it
453 * on every INIT_RAM_RESTRICT_ZM_GROUP opcode.
454 *
455 * Preserving the non-caching behaviour on earlier chipsets just
456 * in case *not* re-reading the strap causes similar breakage.
457 */
458 if (!init->ramcfg || init->bios->version.major < 0x70)
459 init->ramcfg = 0x80000000 | nvbios_ramcfg_index(init->subdev);
460 return (init->ramcfg & 0x7fffffff);
461}

463static u8
464init_xlat_(struct nvbios_init *init, u8 index, u8 offset)
465{
466 struct nvkm_bios *bios = init->bios;
467 u16 table = init_xlat_table(init);
468 if (table) {
469 u16 data = nvbios_rd16(bios, table + (index * 2));
470 if (data)
471 return nvbios_rd08(bios, data + offset);
472 warn("xlat table pointer %d invalid\n", index);
473 }
474 return 0x00;
475}

477/******************************************************************************
478 * utility functions used by various init opcode handlers
479 *****************************************************************************/
480
481static bool
482init_condition_met(struct nvbios_init *init, u8 cond)
483{
484 struct nvkm_bios *bios = init->bios;
485 u16 table = init_condition_table(init);
486 if (table) {
487 u32 reg = nvbios_rd32(bios, table + (cond * 12) + 0);
488 u32 msk = nvbios_rd32(bios, table + (cond * 12) + 4);
489 u32 val = nvbios_rd32(bios, table + (cond * 12) + 8);
490 trace("\t[0x%02x] (R[0x%06x] & 0x%08x) == 0x%08x\n",
491 cond, reg, msk, val);
492 return (init_rd32(init, reg) & msk) == val;
493 }
494 return false;
495}
496
497static bool
498init_io_condition_met(struct nvbios_init *init, u8 cond)
499{
500 struct nvkm_bios *bios = init->bios;
501 u16 table = init_io_condition_table(init);
502 if (table) {
503 u16 port = nvbios_rd16(bios, table + (cond * 5) + 0);
504 u8 index = nvbios_rd08(bios, table + (cond * 5) + 2);
505 u8 mask = nvbios_rd08(bios, table + (cond * 5) + 3);
506 u8 value = nvbios_rd08(bios, table + (cond * 5) + 4);
507 trace("\t[0x%02x] (0x%04x[0x%02x] & 0x%02x) == 0x%02x\n",
508 cond, port, index, mask, value);
509 return (init_rdvgai(init, port, index) & mask) == value;
510 }
511 return false;
512}
513
514static bool
515init_io_flag_condition_met(struct nvbios_init *init, u8 cond)
516{
517 struct nvkm_bios *bios = init->bios;
518 u16 table = init_io_flag_condition_table(init);
519 if (table) {
520 u16 port = nvbios_rd16(bios, table + (cond * 9) + 0);
521 u8 index = nvbios_rd08(bios, table + (cond * 9) + 2);
522 u8 mask = nvbios_rd08(bios, table + (cond * 9) + 3);
523 u8 shift = nvbios_rd08(bios, table + (cond * 9) + 4);
524 u16 data = nvbios_rd16(bios, table + (cond * 9) + 5);
525 u8 dmask = nvbios_rd08(bios, table + (cond * 9) + 7);
526 u8 value = nvbios_rd08(bios, table + (cond * 9) + 8);
527 u8 ioval = (init_rdvgai(init, port, index) & mask) >> shift;
528 return (nvbios_rd08(bios, data + ioval) & dmask) == value;
529 }
530 return false;
531}

533static inline u32
534init_shift(u32 data, u8 shift)
535{
536 if (shift < 0x80)
537 return data >> shift;
538 return data << (0x100 - shift);
539}

541static u32
542init_tmds_reg(struct nvbios_init *init, u8 tmds)
543{
544 /* For mlv < 0x80, it is an index into a table of TMDS base addresses.
545 * For mlv == 0x80 use the "or" value of the dcb_entry indexed by
546 * CR58 for CR57 = 0 to index a table of offsets to the basic
547 * 0x6808b0 address.
548 * For mlv == 0x81 use the "or" value of the dcb_entry indexed by
549 * CR58 for CR57 = 0 to index a table of offsets to the basic
550 * 0x6808b0 address, and then flip the offset by 8.
551 */
552 const int pramdac_offset[13] = {
553 0, 0, 0x8, 0, 0x2000, 0, 0, 0, 0x2008, 0, 0, 0, 0x2000 };
554 const u32 pramdac_table[4] = {
555 0x6808b0, 0x6808b8, 0x6828b0, 0x6828b8 };
556
557 if (tmds >= 0x80) {
558 if (init->outp) {
559 u32 dacoffset = pramdac_offset[init->outp->or];
560 if (tmds == 0x81)
561 dacoffset ^= 8;
562 return 0x6808b0 + dacoffset;
563 }
564
565 if (init_exec(init))
566 error("tmds opcodes need dcb\n");
567 } else {
568 if (tmds < ARRAY_SIZE(pramdac_table))
569 return pramdac_table[tmds];
570
571 error("tmds selector 0x%02x unknown\n", tmds);
572 }
573
574 return 0;
575}

581/**
582 * init_reserved - stub for various unknown/unused single-byte opcodes
583 *
584 */
585static void
586init_reserved(struct nvbios_init *init)
587{
588 u8 opcode = nvbios_rd08(init->bios, init->offset);
589 u8 length, i;
590
591 switch (opcode) {
592 case 0xaa:
593 length = 4;
594 break;
595 default:
596 length = 1;
597 break;
598 }
599
600 trace("RESERVED 0x%02x\t", opcode);
601 for (i = 1; i < length; i++)
602 cont(" 0x%02x", nvbios_rd08(init->bios, init->offset + i));
603 cont("\n");
604 init->offset += length;
605}

618/**
619 * INIT_IO_RESTRICT_PROG - opcode 0x32
620 *
621 */
622static void
623init_io_restrict_prog(struct nvbios_init *init)
624{
625 struct nvkm_bios *bios = init->bios;
626 u16 port = nvbios_rd16(bios, init->offset + 1);
627 u8 index = nvbios_rd08(bios, init->offset + 3);
628 u8 mask = nvbios_rd08(bios, init->offset + 4);
629 u8 shift = nvbios_rd08(bios, init->offset + 5);
630 u8 count = nvbios_rd08(bios, init->offset + 6);
631 u32 reg = nvbios_rd32(bios, init->offset + 7);
632 u8 conf, i;
633
634 trace("IO_RESTRICT_PROG\tR[0x%06x] = "
635 "((0x%04x[0x%02x] & 0x%02x) >> %d) [{\n",
636 reg, port, index, mask, shift);
637 init->offset += 11;
638
639 conf = (init_rdvgai(init, port, index) & mask) >> shift;
640 for (i = 0; i < count; i++) {
641 u32 data = nvbios_rd32(bios, init->offset);
642
643 if (i == conf) {
644 trace("\t0x%08x *\n", data);
645 init_wr32(init, reg, data);
646 } else {
647 trace("\t0x%08x\n", data);
648 }
649
650 init->offset += 4;
651 }
652 trace("}]\n");
653}

655/**
656 * INIT_REPEAT - opcode 0x33
657 *
658 */
659static void
660init_repeat(struct nvbios_init *init)
661{
662 struct nvkm_bios *bios = init->bios;
663 u8 count = nvbios_rd08(bios, init->offset + 1);
664 u16 repeat = init->repeat;
665
666 trace("REPEAT\t0x%02x\n", count);
667 init->offset += 2;
668
669 init->repeat = init->offset;
670 init->repend = init->offset;
671 while (count--) {
672 init->offset = init->repeat;
673 nvbios_exec(init);
674 if (count)
675 trace("REPEAT\t0x%02x\n", count);
676 }
677 init->offset = init->repend;
678 init->repeat = repeat;
679}

681/**
682 * INIT_IO_RESTRICT_PLL - opcode 0x34
683 *
684 */
685static void
686init_io_restrict_pll(struct nvbios_init *init)
687{
688 struct nvkm_bios *bios = init->bios;
689 u16 port = nvbios_rd16(bios, init->offset + 1);
690 u8 index = nvbios_rd08(bios, init->offset + 3);
691 u8 mask = nvbios_rd08(bios, init->offset + 4);
692 u8 shift = nvbios_rd08(bios, init->offset + 5);
693 s8 iofc = nvbios_rd08(bios, init->offset + 6);
694 u8 count = nvbios_rd08(bios, init->offset + 7);
695 u32 reg = nvbios_rd32(bios, init->offset + 8);
696 u8 conf, i;
697
698 trace("IO_RESTRICT_PLL\tR[0x%06x] =PLL= "
699 "((0x%04x[0x%02x] & 0x%02x) >> 0x%02x) IOFCOND 0x%02x [{\n",
700 reg, port, index, mask, shift, iofc);
701 init->offset += 12;
702
703 conf = (init_rdvgai(init, port, index) & mask) >> shift;
704 for (i = 0; i < count; i++) {
705 u32 freq = nvbios_rd16(bios, init->offset) * 10;
706
707 if (i == conf) {
708 trace("\t%dkHz *\n", freq);
709 if (iofc > 0 && init_io_flag_condition_met(init, iofc))
710 freq *= 2;
711 init_prog_pll(init, reg, freq);
712 } else {
713 trace("\t%dkHz\n", freq);
714 }
715
716 init->offset += 2;
717 }
718 trace("}]\n");
719}

793/**
794 * INIT_DP_CONDITION - opcode 0x3a
795 *
796 */
797static void
798init_dp_condition(struct nvbios_init *init)
799{
800 struct nvkm_bios *bios = init->bios;
801 struct nvbios_dpout info;
802 u8 cond = nvbios_rd08(bios, init->offset + 1);
803 u8 unkn = nvbios_rd08(bios, init->offset + 2);
804 u8 ver, hdr, cnt, len;
805 u16 data;
806
807 trace("DP_CONDITION\t0x%02x 0x%02x\n", cond, unkn);
808 init->offset += 3;
809
810 switch (cond) {
811 case 0:
812 if (init_conn(init) != DCB_CONNECTOR_eDP)
813 init_exec_set(init, false);
814 break;
815 case 1:
816 case 2:
817 if ( init->outp &&
818 (data = nvbios_dpout_match(bios, DCB_OUTPUT_DP,
819 (init->outp->or << 0) |
820 (init->outp->sorconf.link << 6),
821 &ver, &hdr, &cnt, &len, &info)))
822 {
823 if (!(info.flags & cond))
824 init_exec_set(init, false);
825 break;
826 }
827
828 if (init_exec(init))
829 warn("script needs dp output table data\n");
830 break;
831 case 5:
832 if (!(init_rdauxr(init, 0x0d) & 1))
833 init_exec_set(init, false);
834 break;
835 default:
836 warn("unknown dp condition 0x%02x\n", cond);
837 break;
838 }
839}

1509
1510static void
1511init_configure_mem(struct nvbios_init *init)
1512{
1513 struct nvkm_bios *bios = init->bios;
1514 u16 mdata, sdata;
1515 u32 addr, data;
1516
1517 trace("CONFIGURE_MEM\n");
1518 init->offset += 1;
1519
1520 if (bios->version.major > 2) {
1521 init_done(init);
1522 return;
1523 }
1524 init_exec_force(init, true);
1525
1526 mdata = init_configure_mem_clk(init);
1527 sdata = bmp_sdr_seq_table(bios);
1528 if (nvbios_rd08(bios, mdata) & 0x01)
1529 sdata = bmp_ddr_seq_table(bios);
1530 mdata += 6; /* skip to data */
1531
1532 data = init_rdvgai(init, 0x03c4, 0x01);
1533 init_wrvgai(init, 0x03c4, 0x01, data | 0x20);
1534
1535 for (; (addr = nvbios_rd32(bios, sdata)) != 0xffffffff; sdata += 4) {
1536 switch (addr) {
1537 case 0x10021c: /* CKE_NORMAL */
1538 case 0x1002d0: /* CMD_REFRESH */
1539 case 0x1002d4: /* CMD_PRECHARGE */
1540 data = 0x00000001;
1541 break;
1542 default:
1543 data = nvbios_rd32(bios, mdata);
1544 mdata += 4;
1545 if (data == 0xffffffff)
1546 continue;
1547 break;
1548 }
1549
1550 init_wr32(init, addr, data);
1551 }
1552
1553 init_exec_force(init, false);
1554}

1556/**
1557 * INIT_CONFIGURE_CLK - opcode 0x67
1558 *
1559 */
1560static void
1561init_configure_clk(struct nvbios_init *init)
1562{
1563 struct nvkm_bios *bios = init->bios;
1564 u16 mdata, clock;
1565
1566 trace("CONFIGURE_CLK\n");
1567 init->offset += 1;

1570 init_done(init);
1571 return;
1572 }

1584 clock *= 2;

1587 init_exec_force(init, false);

2029 * INIT_XLAT - opcode 0x96
2030 *
2031 */
2032static void
2033init_xlat(struct nvbios_init *init)
2034{
2035 struct nvkm_bios *bios = init->bios;
2036 u32 saddr = nvbios_rd32(bios, init->offset + 1);
2037 u8 sshift = nvbios_rd08(bios, init->offset + 5);
2038 u8 smask = nvbios_rd08(bios, init->offset + 6);
2039 u8 index = nvbios_rd08(bios, init->offset + 7);
2040 u32 daddr = nvbios_rd32(bios, init->offset + 8);
2041 u32 dmask = nvbios_rd32(bios, init->offset + 12);
2042 u8 shift = nvbios_rd08(bios, init->offset + 16);
2043 u32 data;
2044
2045 trace("INIT_XLAT\tR[0x%06x] &= 0x%08x |= "
2046 "(X%02x((R[0x%06x] %s 0x%02x) & 0x%02x) << 0x%02x)\n",
2047 daddr, dmask, index, saddr, (sshift & 0x80) ? "<<" : ">>",
2048 (sshift & 0x80) ? (0x100 - sshift) : sshift, smask, shift);
2049 init->offset += 17;
2050
2051 data = init_shift(init_rd32(init, saddr), sshift) & smask;
2052 data = init_xlat_(init, index, data) << shift;
2053 init_mask(init, daddr, ~dmask, data);
2054}

2123/**
2124 * INIT_I2C_LONG_IF - opcode 0x9a
2125 *
2126 */
2127static void
2128init_i2c_long_if(struct nvbios_init *init)
2129{
2130 struct nvkm_bios *bios = init->bios;
2131 u8 index = nvbios_rd08(bios, init->offset + 1);
2132 u8 addr = nvbios_rd08(bios, init->offset + 2) >> 1;
2133 u8 reglo = nvbios_rd08(bios, init->offset + 3);
2134 u8 reghi = nvbios_rd08(bios, init->offset + 4);
2135 u8 mask = nvbios_rd08(bios, init->offset + 5);
2136 u8 data = nvbios_rd08(bios, init->offset + 6);
2137 struct i2c_adapter *adap;
2138
2139 trace("I2C_LONG_IF\t"
2140 "I2C[0x%02x][0x%02x][0x%02x%02x] & 0x%02x == 0x%02x\n",
2141 index, addr, reglo, reghi, mask, data);
2142 init->offset += 7;
2143
2144 adap = init_i2c(init, index);
2145 if (adap) {
2146 u8 i[2] = { reghi, reglo };
2147 u8 o[1] = {};
2148 struct i2c_msg msg[] = {
2149 { .addr = addr, .flags = 0, .len = 2, .buf = i },
2150 { .addr = addr, .flags = I2C_M_RD, .len = 1, .buf = o }
2151 };
2152 int ret;
2153
2154 ret = i2c_transfer(adap, msg, 2);
2155 if (ret == 2 && ((o[0] & mask) == data))
2156 return;
2157 }
2158
2159 init_exec_set(init, false);
2160}

2162/**
2163 * INIT_GPIO_NE - opcode 0xa9
2164 *
2165 */
2166static void
2167init_gpio_ne(struct nvbios_init *init)
2168{
2169 struct nvkm_bios *bios = init->bios;
2170 struct nvkm_gpio *gpio = bios->subdev.device->gpio;
2171 struct dcb_gpio_func func;
2172 u8 count = nvbios_rd08(bios, init->offset + 1);
2173 u8 idx = 0, ver, len;
2174 u16 data, i;
2175
2176 trace("GPIO_NE\t");
2177 init->offset += 2;
2178
2179 for (i = init->offset; i < init->offset + count; i++)
2180 cont("0x%02x ", nvbios_rd08(bios, i));
2181 cont("\n");
2182
2183 while ((data = dcb_gpio_parse(bios, 0, idx++, &ver, &len, &func))) {
2184 if (func.func != DCB_GPIO_UNUSED) {
2185 for (i = init->offset; i < init->offset + count; i++) {
2186 if (func.func == nvbios_rd08(bios, i))
2187 break;
2188 }
2189
2190 trace("\tFUNC[0x%02x]", func.func);
2191 if (i == (init->offset + count)) {
2192 cont(" *");
2193 if (init_exec(init))
2194 nvkm_gpio_reset(gpio, func.func);
2195 }
2196 cont("\n");
2197 }
2198 }
2199
2200 init->offset += count;
2201}

2277#define init_opcode_nr (sizeof(init_opcode) / sizeof(init_opcode[0]))
2278
2279int
2280nvbios_exec(struct nvbios_init *init)
2281{
2282 init->nested++;
2283 while (init->offset) {
2284 u8 opcode = nvbios_rd08(init->bios, init->offset);
2285 if (opcode >= init_opcode_nr || !init_opcode[opcode].exec) {
2286 error("unknown opcode 0x%02x\n", opcode);
2287 return -EINVAL;
2288 }
2289
2290 init_opcode[opcode].exec(init);
2291 }
2292 init->nested--;
2293 return 0;
2294}

2296int
2297nvbios_init(struct nvkm_subdev *subdev, bool execute)
2298{
2299 struct nvkm_bios *bios = subdev->device->bios;
2300 int ret = 0;
2301 int i = -1;
2302 u16 data;
2303
2304 if (execute)
2305 nvkm_debug(subdev, "running init tables\n");
2306 while (!ret && (data = (init_script(bios, ++i)))) {
2307 struct nvbios_init init = {
2308 .subdev = subdev,
2309 .bios = bios,
2310 .offset = data,
2311 .outp = NULL,
2312 .crtc = -1,
2313 .execute = execute ? 1 : 0,
2314 };
2315
2316 ret = nvbios_exec(&init);
2317 }
2318
2319 /* the vbios parser will run this right after the normal init
2320 * tables, whereas the binary driver appears to run it later.
2321 */
2322 if (!ret && (data = init_unknown_script(bios))) {
2323 struct nvbios_init init = {
2324 .subdev = subdev,
2325 .bios = bios,
2326 .offset = data,
2327 .outp = NULL,
2328 .crtc = -1,
2329 .execute = execute ? 1 : 0,
2330 };
2331
2332 ret = nvbios_exec(&init);
2333 }
2334
2335 return ret;
2336}
